caption: Best BBQ in the NE/NW of DC.
The wings in particular are incredible (but really you can't go wrong with most of the menu) and their bottle shop is churning out awesome deals during covid.
I actually enjoy the dishes and service, fantastic area next to where I live. The cashiers are always kind. Highly recommended.
Fantastic food, very friendly staff members, regularly fantastic mood. They charge convenient pricing and the food quality is awesome. I recommend this place.

Phenomenal! Great selection of bourbon and whiskies. A good discount on six packs of cans for takeaway. Outstanding brisket (particularly with the Texas red sauce). Peppery mac and cheese. Remarkably, the chicken tenders (a kids menu item) have got to be the best we’ve ever tasted. For a barbecue joint to take such care and pride for a kids menu item really says something great about how much the staff and kitchen and owners care about their customers.

The sandwiches had a nice bun and an ample serving of meat that was pretty tough and weak in flavor. Potato salad was good, but expensive for the portion size. The brisket chili was just ok—honestly no better than Wendy's chili. Try Backyard Smokespot for tastier, less gentrified BBQ.

Well organized and laid out walk up window to order pick up food! All staff, especially John, were kind, friendly, and attentive the second I arrived at the window. There was even an outdoor heater to stay under while you wait for your food. The pulled pork sandwich with a side of Mac and cheese really turned around my day!

The super awesome take out window is a perfect stop on an evening walk! The mulled wine is delicious and the pork rinds are a must-have. The staff are so kind and helpful too making it an all around great stop.
Awesome food, people and drinks. Brisket, wings, beef ribs are all awesome. They even have a chorizo burger. Awesome place.
Love this place!
My fav location for tasty BBQ. I was so full.
The brisket was not sliced, it was chopped, and the wings were very small, though they had a good dry rub.
So good and the staff are super cool. The pick up window is fun - beer and booze for sale to take home with your order.
Love this place! So fresh and flavorful. And the people are really wonderful. Fried chicken sandwich is 🥰
I ordered the Brisket. It was juicy, rich and delicious. The sprouts were also a nice sad to get some veggies with all that meat. Highly recommend this cute place.

Feel really lucky to have Cinder BBQ nearby during these crazy times. Their wonderful BBQ is such great comfort food for a great price. Don't sleep on their dry rub wings or the cauliflower entree which is delicious. Great sauce choices to compliment their tasty BBQ. Definitely indulge when I can.

This our second time ordering food for pickup. Once again, the food and service were right on. Even with covid concerns, pick up was easy, clean, contactless and friendly/professional. We will order from them again.
Super moist pulled pork sandwich. Generous portions. The mac and cheese was also on point. Looking forward to coming back.

We ordered a family pack, which is a tremendous value. The brisket and chicken were both tender and moist, and paired very well with the sauce options even though I generally like thicker sauces. I loved Cinder's take on baked beans and coleslaw, which really differentiated the meal from other restaurants in a good way. If you aren't a fan of mayo-heavy slaw, this is the slaw for you. The mac and cheese was also delicious.  We shouldn't have waited so long to try Cinder and we'll definitely be ordering again soon.

Amazing neighborhood spot! The bartenders and owners are always really nice and they've been extremely careful with contract-less pickup and sanitizing during the current COVID pandemic. The brussels sprouts are must-haves along with the wings!

We've ordered from Cinder multiple times and always been happy with the experience.  The food is great and the staff has always been enthusiastic.  We expect to continue doing a lot of business with Cinder in the future.

This place has been in our neighborhood for a while and we finally got around to trying it. What took us so long? At first the food didn't look like much for the price, but it turns out brisket and pulled chicken go a long way with the sides and the buns. The pick-up operation had good COVID protections and the manager was super friendly. Bonus: I bought a six pack of Genesee Cream Ale (although I though it was a little steep at $10). We are definitely going back soon for a pandemic safe picnic.

My family is always very pleased with the food (my son loves the wings), and the staff couldn't be friendlier and more service-oriented - a very community-based restaurant. Great whiskey selection too!
Local staple. Great food, outstanding staff.
I love having Cinder in the Petworth neighborhood! Everyone is super friendly and the BBQ is delicious!
Simply put, it’s BBQ done right!!!

Our whole family loves to get take-out from Cinder. We appreciate the high-quality of their meats and sides and variety of sauces. Be sure not to miss the wings, which are hands down our favorite! Even our finicky 8-year old gives Cinder two big thumbs up.  While we greatly miss being able to dine in the restaurant, we appreciate the care and attention the folks at Cinder put into making take-out safe during Covid-19.
Great food, great drinks, great people!

As the Pit Master’s granddaughter, I’m telling you Cinder BBQ makes everything taste good! I have had my grandfather’s cooking for years and years, and he has made me come to love many different foods. I hate cole slaw, but I love his! The brisket sandwich is amazing with his signature barbecue sauces, and the baked beans are just the right amount of spicy and sweet.
Friendly staff, the best wings in town, and they are doing a great job of being safe during these crazy times.  They are a great asset to the neighborhood.
We have ordered the Saturday night special  2 times could not be happier what a terrific deal. the ribs are out of this world . The staff could not be friendlier . Excellent customer service.

I was very disappointed with the BBQ here. This place pales in comparison to places like texas jacks, Federalist Pig etc.  I was warned about this place but I was in the neighborhood so I figured Id try it. Maybe go for drinks but definitely not the food.

Great place in a very nice neighborhood. The pulled pork sandwich with french fries was delicious, excellent meat and potato bread, tasty bbq sauce, and good prices. I’d wish it opens earlier for lunch and closes later for dinner.
Really good BBQ!

Can’t say enough good things about Cinder and it’s owners John & Matt! They care about creating both a great barbecue product and a great environment for the community. As a Georgia Ave business owner I am excited to see other truly local businesses who want to grow and invest in Petworth continue to pop up. Stop by and try their brisket it’s fantastic!!
I had an excellent time in this place. We enjoyed the awesome atmosphere and the food. The waiters are very affable. I am content we ultimately decided to try this place.

Cinder BBQ is both a great bar and great barbecue joint. The sandwiches are simple but made with excellent potato bread and, of course, a dollop of their excellent barbecue. Simple presentation with just a bit of pickles and coleslaw to add or not. Excellent house-made hot sauces. Great bar selection with plenty of seats and friendly staff.
Cinder BBQ was fabulous. I great time . The atmosphere was cool and laid back, and the food delicious!
The food was good! Especially the smoked wings.
This restaurant gives fantastic service and enjoyable food. The best spot in the area. The drinks and food served rapidly and the rates were fair. Will definitely recommend this spot.

Three stars seems too low and four stars seems too high so I'm going to give it a four anyway.  Ultimately the food was just okay. The ribs were stringy and the cauliflower was overwhelmingly limey so the meals didn't end up being the main draw. The sides were arguably better, with well made mac & cheese and brussel sprouts. I did enjoy their ample bev options, both alcoholic and non, and if you're a whiskey lover of any form you'll be happy here. (great bourbon selection!)  The space is very cool and occupies a nice city block that's starting to see its staple locations close. I could see this place being beloved as a neighborhood spot and I'd definitely pop back in if I were in the area.
Great whiskey selection, great barbeque. The brussel sprouts are one of my favorite.

This is the best brisket I've ever had, hands down. The sides are pretty good, too, though the meat is just intoxicating. They also have a small but stellar whiskey selection. Huge addition to the neighborhood.
Best brisket I've ever had. Knowledgeable bartenders. Cozy too.
Outstanding old fashioned.  Really good BBQ.  Great service.
Good is good.  I think the wings are heavy on the seasoning.  Bartender named Rain is polite, knowledgeable and of course cute
We're there with family. Shared 5 different entrees and sides and everything was very good!
Phenomenal food (some of the best BBQ I've had), welcoming, friendly people. What more could you ask for?!
Good food, great drinks, lovely people...in the neighborhood!
Best meal in DC!!! Owner and chef chatted with us. We came in with a group of 8 that they accommodated quickly. Food was out of this world. This will be my new weekly watering hole!!
Very good brisket. Great selection of bourbons
Cant say enough about this place. Beyond tasty. Dry rub wings appear in my dreams now and my veggie loving friends enjoyed their food too.
Great BBQ experience with a neighborhood feel. Definitely the type of place you want to go back to. Great food, competitive prices and friendly staff.
The food here is incredible. Everything on the menu is delicious but the brisket is outstanding. Easily one of the best BBQ places in DC.
Very average BBQ. No major complaints but nothing to rave about either. Pretty nice ambiance and pretty solid service. But, the food wasn’t exceptionally special.
Fantastic bbq, creative twist on chicken wings, friendly folks

Here you’ll find a brisket fit for the gods. It’s a transcendent experience. They’ll offer you sauces to put on it, but using them would be a bit like looking at a Caravaggio through sunglasses. Save it for the ribs, which are also excellent.

This is the best BBQ restaurant in DC! I can’t tell you how long I have been waiting for a BBQ restaurant that actually tastes good ( I have tried all of them) these folks got it right and the prices are great.  I also loved the look and location of the restaurant. It’s located in a nice neighborhood of ppl. I actually think everyone in that neighborhood will go there for family dinner because every time I go I see someone walking out of their house with their family to the restaurant lol.  The service is awesome. The folks really take care of you even when the restaurant is crazy busy. Everyone there has an inviting smile on their face.  I suggest that you get to the restaurant early and try their wings. I can honestly say you will never find anything like it! The flavors are sooo good.  I know it might sound crazy but you must try the Brussels spouts. I could never eat these as a child but I saw some one eating these so I asked them if they were good and they said yes. i figured everything else was good so why not try them. I swear these will have you trying to figure out how they made Brussels sprouts taste like heaven haha .  I give this place an A++ and I highly recommend you check it out when you are in DC.
Very good value. Carefully cooked food. Not overly loud. Many choices of bourbon by the glass. " Good cooking for its type."
Just OK. You have to get up and go to the bar to order. The portion for the sandwich was just adequate and not too flavorful. The sauce was weak.
The service was great although I felt that some of the entries were a little pricey.
The wings were great!
Brisket is delicious. The side of coleslaw and homemade pickle slices are also very tasty. Friendly team.
Excellent BBQ...Melt In Your Mouth Brisket n Great Service & Staff....And Bill & John Thank You Excellent First Visit to go with Wonderful Food!! Shout Rain as well
Food was delicious.  We tried pulled pork and brisket with collard greens and onion rings.  Good drinks if on the small side.  Great whiskey selection.
Awesome BBQ also great staff and environment
I had the brisket. It was beautifully cooked with a great texture, but it just didn't have much of a smoked flavor.  The sides were good. The collard greens were particularly good.
Glad to have Cinder BBQ in the neighborhood

The half smoke is fine. The pork rinds were great. Everything else... oooooofffff. Brisket was dry and chewy. Slaw is rough. Green beans were a crime. I'm hoping it comes around but oompah loompah not a fan.
Stellar BBQ - loved the sauces. Great to have a nea family friendly spot in the neighborhood. Staff were really accommodating. We'll be back!
Drinks are well priced, wings are great. Brisket sandwich was good. I wish they had a sampler platter, but everything we had was either good or delicious.

Hands-down the best BBQ experience EVER.  Chicken wings are divine - a dry-rub, juicy tender masterpiece.  These Texans know how brisket should be cooked and served.  Will I travel 452 miles again to eat at Cinder?  ABSOLUTELY.
Incredible bbq in DC

This place is seriously legit BBQ. Their focus is on Texas BBQ where beef is King. I had the brisket with mac and cheese, both were standouts. The beer and burbon selection were well curated.  Service was attentive featuring counter based ordering complemented by supplemental table service.

FOOD COMA WHILE WRITING THIS REVIEW! I have never eaten so much in one night! Loved the onion rings and half smoked chicken - so tender. Can’t live without the Spicy Redemption sauce! The sauce the green beans came in was amazing. Can’t wait to go back soon!

THE BEST WINGS OF MY LIFE. Bill, the pitmaster, came out and made sure we had everything we needed twice. The garlic kale salad is amazing, I never liked pickles before came here, they even made a good margarita! The brisket literally melted in my mouth and I wanted to steal the Apple cider BBQ sauce. Amazing experience.
The brisket here is incredible. Look at this juicy goodness.
